---
dops: v1
kind: tool

meta:
  name: kubernetes
  version: 1.0.0
  description: "Generate Kubernetes deployment manifests"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [k8s, kubernetes, container, orchestration, deployment]

input:
  fields:
    appName:
      type: string
      required: true
    image:
      type: string
      required: true
    port:
      type: integer
      required: true
      min: 1
    replicas:
      type: integer
      default: 1
      min: 1
    namespace:
      type: string
      default: "default"
    outputPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Directory to write Kubernetes manifests to (e.g. './k8s')"
    environment:
      type: string

output:
  type: object
  required: [deployment, service]
  properties:
    deployment:
      type: object
      required: [replicas, containers]
      properties:
        replicas:
          type: number
        containers:
          type: array
          minItems: 1
          items:
            type: object
            required: [name, image, ports]
            properties:
              name:
                type: string
              image:
                type: string
              ports:
                type: array
                minItems: 1
                items:
                  type: object
                  required: [containerPort]
                  properties:
                    containerPort:
                      type: number
                    protocol:
                      type: string
              env:
                type: array
                items:
                  type: object
                  required: [name]
                  properties:
                    name:
                      type: string
                    value:
                      type: string
                    valueFrom:
                      type: object
              resources:
                type: object
                properties:
                  requests:
                    type: object
                  limits:
                    type: object
              livenessProbe:
                type: object
              readinessProbe:
                type: object
              securityContext:
                type: object
              volumeMounts:
                type: array
                items:
                  type: object
        labels:
          type: object
    service:
      type: object
      required: [ports]
      properties:
        type:
          type: string
          enum: [ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer]
        ports:
          type: array
          minItems: 1
          items:
            type: object
            required: [port, targetPort]
            properties:
              port:
                type: number
              targetPort:
                type: number
              protocol:
                type: string
              name:
                type: string
    configMaps:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          data:
            type: object
    secrets:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        required: [name]
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
          type:
            type: string
          data:
            type: object
    ingress:
      type: object
    hpa:
      type: object
    statefulSet:
      type: object
    daemonSet:
      type: object
    cronJob:
      type: object
    pvcs:
      type: array
    rbac:
      type: object
    networkPolicy:
      type: object
    pdb:
      type: object

files:
  - path: "{outputPath}/{appName}.yaml"
    format: yaml
    source: llm
    multiDocument: true
    options:
      sortKeys: true
      lineWidth: 120

detection:
  paths: ["*.yaml", "*.yml", "k8s/*.yaml", "k8s/*.yml", "kubernetes/*.yaml"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "deployment"
      required: true
      message: "Deployment configuration is required"
    - path: "deployment.containers"
      type: array
      minItems: 1
      message: "Deployment must define at least one container"
    - path: "deployment.containers.*.name"
      required: true
      message: "Each container must have a name"
    - path: "deployment.containers.*.image"
      required: true
      message: "Each container must have an image"
    - path: "service"
      required: true
      message: "Service configuration is required"
    - path: "service.ports"
      type: array
      minItems: 1
      message: "Service must define at least one port"

  binary:
    command: "kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifest.yaml"
    parser: kubectl-stderr
    timeout: 30000
    cwd: output

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: required
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["{outputPath}/{appName}.yaml"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "Cluster configuration changes affect running services"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# Kubernetes

## Prompt

You are a Kubernetes expert. Generate Kubernetes deployment manifests as structured JSON.

Respond with a JSON object containing deployment and service configurations:
{
  "deployment": {
    "replicas": 1,
    "containers": [
      {
        "name": "app",
        "image": "nginx:latest",
        "ports": [{ "containerPort": 80, "protocol": "TCP" }],
        "env": [],
        "resources": {
          "requests": { "cpu": "100m", "memory": "128Mi" },
          "limits": { "cpu": "500m", "memory": "256Mi" }
        }
      }
    ],
    "labels": { "app": "my-app" }
  },
  "service": {
    "type": "ClusterIP",
    "ports": [{ "port": 80, "targetPort": 80, "protocol": "TCP" }]
  },
  "configMaps": [],
  "secrets": []
}

IMPORTANT:
- "deployment" and "service" are required
- "containers" must be an ARRAY with at least one container
- Each container must have "name", "image", and "ports"
- Include resource requests/limits for production readiness
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Update Prompt

You are a Kubernetes expert. Update existing Kubernetes manifests.
Preserve existing resources and settings. Only add/modify what is requested.

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

Respond with valid JSON containing the full deployment and service configuration.

IMPORTANT:
- Preserve ALL existing containers, volumes, and configurations
- Maintain existing labels and annotations
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Examples

Given: "Deploy nginx with 3 replicas on port 80"

```json
{
  "deployment": {
    "replicas": 3,
    "containers": [
      {
        "name": "nginx",
        "image": "nginx:1.25",
        "ports": [{ "containerPort": 80, "protocol": "TCP" }],
        "env": [],
        "resources": {
          "requests": { "cpu": "100m", "memory": "128Mi" },
          "limits": { "cpu": "500m", "memory": "256Mi" }
        }
      }
    ],
    "labels": { "app": "nginx" }
  },
  "service": {
    "type": "ClusterIP",
    "ports": [{ "port": 80, "targetPort": 80, "protocol": "TCP" }]
  },
  "configMaps": [],
  "secrets": []
}
```

## Constraints

- Always include resource requests and limits
- Use specific image tags, not :latest in production
- Container names must be lowercase alphanumeric with hyphens
- Include liveness and readiness probes for production workloads
- Use non-root security context when possible

## Keywords

kubernetes, k8s, kubectl, deployment, service, pod, container,
namespace, ingress, configmap, secret, hpa, statefulset, daemonset,
helm, kustomize, manifest, yaml, orchestration
